---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import SiteFooter from '../components/SiteFooter.astro';
import SiteHeader from '../components/SiteHeader.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Terms &amp; Conditions — AfterWage"
  description="The terms under which this calculator is offered. Plain-language version of the standard disclaimers."
>
  <SiteHeader theme="light" />

  <main class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 pt-28 pb-16 md:pt-32 md:pb-24">
    <a href="/" class="block font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-mute hover:text-blood">
      &larr; Back to the calculator
    </a>

    <h1 class="font-display font-light text-5xl md:text-6xl tracking-tightest mt-8 mb-6">
      Terms &amp; Conditions
    </h1>

    <p class="font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-mute mb-10">
      Last updated: April 18, 2026
    </p>

    <p class="font-display italic text-2xl text-ink-soft mb-16 leading-snug">
      The legal terms of using this calculator, in as little legalese as possible.
    </p>

    <article class="prose-custom space-y-10 font-body text-lg leading-relaxed">
      <section>
        <h2 class="font-display font-light text-3xl tracking-tightest mb-4">
          Agreement
        </h2>
        <p>
          By using this site, you agree to these terms. If you do not agree,
          please do not use the site. These terms apply to the entire site
          including the calculator, share image generator, and all supporting
          pages.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="font-display font-light text-3xl tracking-tightest mb-4">
          This is not financial, tax, or legal advice
        </h2>
        <p>
          The calculator produces estimates based on the inputs you provide
          and publicly available tax data. It is intended for general
          information and personal reflection only. It is not:
        </p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 list-disc pl-6">
          <li>Financial advice</li>
          <li>Tax advice or a tax filing tool</li>
          <li>Legal advice</li>
          <li>A substitute for professional consultation with a
              qualified accountant, financial advisor, or tax
              professional</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Tax laws and rates change. State-level tax rates used in the
          calculator are flat approximations, not full progressive
          brackets. The calculation ignores many real-world factors
          including pre-tax retirement contributions, HSA contributions,
          itemized deductions, tax credits, local and city taxes, and
          employer-provided benefits. Do not use this tool to make tax
          filing decisions or to plan your personal finances in any
          binding way. Consult a licensed professional for advice specific
          to your situation.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="font-display font-light text-3xl tracking-tightest mb-4">
          No warranty
        </h2>
        <p>
          The site is provided "as is" and "as available." We make no
          representation or warranty, express or implied, about the accuracy,
          completeness, reliability, suitability, or availability of the
          site or the information it produces. Your use of the site is at
          your own risk.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="font-display font-light text-3xl tracking-tightest mb-4">
          Limitation of liability
        </h2>
        <p>
          To the fullest extent permitted by law, the operator of this site
          shall not be liable for any direct, indirect, incidental,
          consequential, or punitive damages arising out of your access to
          or use of the site, including but not limited to damages arising
          from your reliance on any information produced by the calculator.
          This limitation applies even if we have been advised of the
          possibility of such damages.
        </p>
        <p>
          Some jurisdictions do not allow the exclusion of certain
          warranties or limitations on liability. In those jurisdictions,
          our liability is limited to the maximum extent permitted by law.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="font-display font-light text-3xl tracking-tightest mb-4">
          Acceptable use
        </h2>
        <p>
          You may use the calculator for personal, non-commercial purposes.
          You may share the results, including the share images generated
          by the site, freely, including on social media and in
          personal communications.
        </p>
        <p>
          You may not:
        </p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 list-disc pl-6">
          <li>Use the site in any way that violates applicable law</li>
          <li>Attempt to interfere with the site's operation, including
              through automated scraping, denial-of-service attempts, or
              exploitation of vulnerabilities</li>
          <li>Use the site to harass, defame, or impersonate others</li>
          <li>Remove or alter any copyright, trademark, or attribution
              notices in share images or other exported content</li>
          <li>Rehost or republish substantial portions of the calculator's
              code or content as your own</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="font-display font-light text-3xl tracking-tightest mb-4">
          Intellectual property
        </h2>
        <p>
          The design, copy, calculation logic, and brand of this site are
          owned by the operator. The concept of the "real hourly wage"
          itself comes from the 1992 book <em>Your Money or Your Life</em>
          by Vicki Robin and Joe Dominguez, to which this site makes no
          ownership claim. Our implementation of that concept is ours.
        </p>
        <p>
          You are free to quote small portions of the site with
          attribution, and to share generated share images as they appear.
          You may not reproduce the site's code, visual design, or
          catalog content in a commercial product without written
          permission.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="font-display font-light text-3xl tracking-tightest mb-4">
          Third-party services
        </h2>
        <p>
          The site uses Google Analytics and Google AdSense, as described
          in our{' '}
          <a href="/privacy" class="underline decoration-blood decoration-2 underline-offset-4 hover:text-blood">
            Privacy Policy
          </a>
          . Your use of the site is also subject to Google's own terms. We
          are not responsible for the content or practices of third-party
          services, including the ads displayed by AdSense or the external
          sites they link to.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="font-display font-light text-3xl tracking-tightest mb-4">
          Changes to the site or these terms
        </h2>
        <p>
          We may change, suspend, or discontinue any part of the site at
          any time, without notice. We may also update these terms. The
          "last updated" date at the top of this page reflects the most
          recent revision. Continued use of the site after changes
          constitutes acceptance of the updated terms.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="font-display font-light text-3xl tracking-tightest mb-4">
          Governing law
        </h2>
        <p>
          These terms are governed by the laws of the Province of Ontario
          and the federal laws of Canada applicable therein, without
          reference to conflict of law principles. Any disputes arising
          from or relating to these terms or your use of the site shall be
          resolved in the courts of Ontario, Canada, and you consent to
          the jurisdiction of those courts.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="font-display font-light text-3xl tracking-tightest mb-4">
          Severability
        </h2>
        <p>
          If any provision of these terms is found to be unenforceable, the
          remaining provisions will continue in full force and effect.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="font-display font-light text-3xl tracking-tightest mb-4">Contact</h2>
        <p>
          Questions about these terms go through the{' '}
          <a href="/contact" class="underline decoration-blood decoration-2 underline-offset-4 hover:text-blood">
            contact form
          </a>
          .
        </p>
      </section>
      <section class="border-t border-ink/10 pt-10 mt-10">
        <h2 class="font-display font-light text-3xl tracking-tightest mb-6">
          Related
        </h2>
        <ul class="space-y-3 text-base">
          <li>
            <a href="/privacy" class="font-display text-xl underline decoration-blood decoration-2 underline-offset-4 hover:text-blood">Privacy Policy</a>
            <span class="text-mute"> &mdash; what (little) data the site collects and how it's used.</span>
          </li>
          <li>
            <a href="/methodology" class="font-display text-xl underline decoration-blood decoration-2 underline-offset-4 hover:text-blood">Methodology</a>
            <span class="text-mute"> &mdash; what the calculator does and explicitly doesn't claim to do.</span>
          </li>
          <li>
            <a href="/contact" class="font-display text-xl underline decoration-blood decoration-2 underline-offset-4 hover:text-blood">Contact</a>
            <span class="text-mute"> &mdash; questions about these terms.</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>
    </article>

    <footer class="mt-24 pt-12 border-t border-ink/10">
      <a href="/" class="btn-primary">Back to the calculator</a>
    </footer>
  </main>

  <SiteFooter />
</Base>

<style is:global>
  .prose-custom h2 { margin-top: 2rem; }
  .prose-custom strong { font-weight: 600; color: #1A1A1A; }
  .prose-custom em { font-style: italic; }
  .prose-custom ul { margin: 1rem 0; }
  .prose-custom li { margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
</style>
